DATA CLOUD
Product Subject Area

The Customer 360 Data Model product subject area defines anything you plan to sell or any part of a product to track for service purposes.

To view a larger version, right-click or control-click the image and select “Open Image in New Tab” or view the Product data model architecture.

The following objects from the Product subject area are represented in Data Cloud.

Product
DMO	DESCRIPTION	REFERENCE DOC LINK
Brand	A Data Cloud DMO for the product’s brand, for example, Northern Trail Outfitters.	Brand DMO Reference
Goods Product	A Data Cloud DMO for a specific product, for example, a carton of milk or a set of towels	Goods Product DMO Reference
Product Catalog
DMO	DESCRIPTION	REFERENCE DOC LINK
Product Catalog	A Data Cloud DMO for a company’s inventory or merchandising catalog.	Product Catalog DMO Reference
Product Catalog Category	A Data Cloud DMO for the category of the product catalog, for example, shoes, trucks or housewares.	Product Catalog Category DMO Reference
Product Category	A Data Cloud DMO for the types of products a company has or offers, like shoes or types of services.	Product Category DMO Reference
Product Category Product	A Data Cloud DMO used to identify how products are assigned to categories. For example, Northern Trail Outfitter’s could use this DMO to identify how a specific running shoe could be assigned to both a shoe and running categories.	Product Category Product DMO Reference
